  "text": "Rheumatoid arthritis as common inflammatory arthritis affects 0.5 to 1% population worldwide. 1 In Canadian study it was found that these patients had 17 years shorter median survival than general population, due to increased prevalence of comorbidities like myocardial infarction, stroke and heart failure. [CITATION_1] In RA estimated prevalence of hypertension was (70.5%).",
